generateUniqueInstanceData

public static void generateUniqueInstanceData(File outFile,
                                              int nEntries,
                                              int nFeaturesPerEntry)
                                       throws IOException
Routine that creates a large amount of data, that should be the absolute worst case for counting stage of the pipeline. That is data where entries and features only ever appear once, and consequently events also are unique. This causes the counting maps to be at the upper bound of their potential size.

Throws:
IOException
